The paper proposes a game-theoretic approach to modeling vehicle interactions in urban traffic environments with unsignalized intersections, which is relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO) research. The focus on autonomous vehicle control verification and validation suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. The use of simulation and optimization techniques indicates a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
